      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROMEO MONTANA (6) goes very well at the distance with two wins and a placing from four starts. Recorded a 13 length win (30.17) in a Mix 6/7 last time at The Meadows. Looks a key chance on best form. MAJOR IMPACT (1) is rarely out of the finish, recording 10 places from 17 starts. Filled a minor placings again last time when third (30.21) at this track making it three placings in a row. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Overdue and gets his chance. SKATE IN PARIS (2) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Turn Up Turbo (30.07) in a Mix 6/7. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from her last run stacks up well. Bold showing expected. VICTORY ALBERT (8) will run well despite no experience on this track.",
